Morane-Saulnier type N (SFA MS642) (5196 RFC)
Morane N, SFA MS642, was flown from Paris to 2 AD Candas by Lt T. P. H. Bayetto of No 3 Squadron on 9 April 1916.
First reported with No 60 Squadron RFC on 22 July 1916.
2 AD ex No 60 Squadron on 21 September 1916.
1 AD ex 2 AD on 24 September 1916.
Despatched to England 'for reconstruction' on 11 October 1916.
